AESTHETIC PERSONAL SOFTWARE TURNS STRESS INTO CREATIVE COMPOSURE
 
Portland, Oregon.  March 1, 1989.  Visionary Software released
"SYNCHRONICITY(TM)," intuitive decision-making software that uses fine art and
soothing sounds to help Macintosh* users turn stress into a calm state of
creative composure.
 
SYNCHRONICITY consists of a series of fine art screens that guide the user
through a personal insight process based on the Book of Changes and the
research of Carl Jung, the famous psychologist, who coined the term.   After 30
years of research, Jung formally discovered and defined "synchronicity" as the
"a causal connecting principle" that lies behind seemingly coincidental events.
 
Visionary Software's product is designed as a practical tool to help reduce the
stress that accompanies tough personal decisions.  "Almost daily, most of us
find ourselves in situations that test our wits, faced with response-choices
that have to made quickly.  Decisions that involve timing, sensitive
relationships, or threats to our security simply do not lend themselves to
logical solutions," said Paul O'Brien, Visionary Software's president.  "That's
where SYNCHRONICITY comes in.  In a playful but serious way, it help users to
calm down, clarify, and resolve dilemmas in their own minds before  reacting.
It does this by mirroring their own natural intuitive insight," he added.
 
Visionary Software chose the Mac as a development platform, because "we
perceived that more creative professionals use that machine than any other.
And creative professionals are most apt to appreciate the benefits of an
intuitively stimulating exercise that's fun to use."
 
SYNCHRONICITY helps users in four ways 1) to achieve greater clarity around a
question, issue, or dilemma; 2) to reinforce skillful detachment by helping
users disengage themselves from situations long enough to reduce the stress and
enhance objectivity; 3) to stimulate intuition, through a response based on a
very wide perspective, for better decisions, and 4) to provide a relaxing but
focused break from the hectic pace of the workday.
 
SYNCHRONICITY accomplishes this in the context of an enjoyable "ritual" that
takes a question and produces a "reading" in response to it.  The reading is
selected on the basis of the unique pattern produced by the user in the ritual
process.  According to O'Brien, "Jung proved that the system really works.
SYNCHRONICITY accomplishes its objectives even if the user doesn't buy into the
literal content of any particular reading.  At the very least, it helps us see
the opportunity in what we may currently be perceiving as a 'problem.'  A tool
that can do that for you, any time you want, is worth a lot more than $49.95."
 
SYNCHRONICITY is immediately available from Visionary Software.   A demo
version of the program is available for $5 including shipping, with full credit
toward purchase.  List price is $49.95 with discounts for students, user group
members, developers, and others who promise to distribute copies of the demo
version.
 
